flavor_text_entries.red:
Although long
extinct, in rare
cases, it can be genetically
resurrected from
fossils.
flavor_text_entries.blue:
Although long
extinct, in rare
cases, it can be genetically
resurrected from
fossils.
flavor_text_entries.yellow:
An ancient POKéMON
that was recovered
from a fossil. It swims by cleverly
twisting its 10
tentacles about.
flavor_text_entries.gold:
Revived from an
ancient fossil,
this POKéMON uses air stored in its
shell to sink and
rise in water.
flavor_text_entries.silver:
This POKéMON from
ancient times is
said to have navi­ gated the sea by
adeptly twisting
its 10 tentacles.
flavor_text_entries.crystal:
In prehistoric
times, it swam on
the sea floor, eating plankton.
Its fossils are
sometimes found.
flavor_text_entries.ruby:
OMANYTE is one of the ancient and long-
since-extinct POKéMON that have been
regenerated from fossils by people. If attacked by an enemy, it withdraws
itself inside its hard shell.

flavor_text_entries.ultra-sun:
Omanyte lived in the seas of antiquity. Its
fossils have been found bearing bite marks from
Archeops, so apparently Archeops preyed on it.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-moon:
It was restored from an ancient fossil. Those
Helix Fossils are excavated from areas that
were once oceans long, long ago.
flavor_text_entries.lets-go-pikachu:

a fossil. It swam by cleverly twisting its
10 tentacles about.

flavor_text_entries.sword:
Because some Omanyte manage to escape after
being restored or are released into the wild by
people, this species is becoming a problem.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
This Pokémon is a member of an ancient, extinct
species. Omanyte paddles through water with its
10 tentacles, looking like it’s just drifting along.
